2026-04-23 | Sum of Distances Between Equal Elements

Question
Return array arr where arr[i] is total distance.
	Key Insight
Brute force is O(n²) → too slow  
Instead:
→ group indices by value  
→ process each group using prefix sums  
	Approach
1.	Map value → list of indices  
2.	For each group:
		let indices = v  
3.	Build prefix sum:
		prefix[i] = sum of indices up to i  
4.	For each index k in group:
		left contribution:
			k * v[k] - prefix[k-1]  
		right contribution:
			(prefix[last] - prefix[k]) - (size-k-1)*v[k]  
5.	Add both  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> distance(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        unordered_map<int, vector<int>> mp;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            mp[nums[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        vector<long long> ans(n, 0);
        for(auto &p : mp){
            auto &v = p.second;
            int m = v.size();
            vector<long long> prefix(m);
            prefix[0] = v[0];
            for(int i = 1; i < m; i++){
                prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + v[i];
            }
            for(int i = 0; i < m; i++){
                long long left = 0, right = 0;
                if(i > 0){
                    left = (long long)v[i] * i - prefix[i-1];
                }
                if(i < m-1){
                    right = (prefix[m-1] - prefix[i]) -
                            (long long)(m - i - 1) * v[i];
                }
                ans[v[i]] = left + right;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
For each value:
		process all its indices together  
Prefix sums allow:
		computing total distances in O(1) per index  
This reduces complexity from O(n²) → O(n).
